Comment.create(id: '1285', tool_id: '268', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on Parser 1.0 and its use is available in the following article:</p> <p>Francis, Alexander L. \"Technical Review: Parser 1.0: An Elementary Parsing Program for the DOS Environment.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 27.5-6 (1993): 406-409. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204567\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 21:37:06', created_at: '2013-05-23 22:00:58', )
Comment.create(id: '1286', tool_id: '250', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on the General Inquirer and its use is available in the following:</p> <p>Dengler, Ralph. \"A General Inquirer Analysis of Sixteenth Century and Contemporary Catechisms.\" <em>Computers and the Humanitie</em>s 8.1 (1974): 5-19. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402453\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Kadushin, Charles, Joseph Lovett and James D. Merriman. \"Literary Analysis with the Aid of the Computer.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 2.4 (1968): 177-202. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402487\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Psathas, George. \"The General Inquirer: Useful or Not?\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 3.3 (1969): 163-174. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02401609\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Rice, Sandra. \"Software Review: INQUIRER III (Edinburgh Edition) A Computer Based System for Content Analysis.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 10.6 (1976): 332. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402556\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Stone, Philip J., Dexter C. Dunphy, Marshall S. Smith and Daniel M. Ogilvie. <em>The General Inquirer: A Computer Approach to Content Analysis</em>. Cambridge: MIT Press, 1966.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-16 18:56:14', created_at: '2013-05-24 20:05:16', )
Comment.create(id: '1287', tool_id: '269', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on FANGORN, its use and its development is available in the following article:</p> <p>Anderson, Peter B&oslash;gh. \"FANGORN: A Special-Purpose Language for the Humanities.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 15.4 (1981): 227-242. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204310\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2014-01-14 19:03:58', created_at: '2013-05-24 20:18:17', )
Comment.create(id: '1288', tool_id: '270', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on STASEL, its use and development is available in an article by two of the developers:</p> <p>Payette, Julie and Graeme Hirst. \"An Intelligent Computer-Assistant for Stylistic Instruction.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 26.2 (1992): 87-102. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204449\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 21:46:13', created_at: '2013-05-24 20:30:51', )
Comment.create(id: '1289', tool_id: '271', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on the Morfogen, Morffile/Morfword and Inflword package, and its use, is available in the following articles:</p> <p>Kyunghwan, Kim. \"Technical Review: Morfogen, Morffile/Morfword, Inflword, Version 2.0.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 27.2 (1993): 133-135. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204485\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>\"Morfogen: A Morphological Analysis and Dictionary Interface Tool.\" Vicky A. Walsh, ed. <em>ACH Newsletter</em> 13.2 (1991): 8. Print.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-21 17:54:24', created_at: '2013-05-24 20:52:42', )
Comment.create(id: '1290', tool_id: '272', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on E-Parser, its use and its development is available in the following article:</p> <p>Nordgard, Torbjorn. \"E-Parser: An Implementation of a Deterministic GB-Related Parsing System.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 28.4-5 (1995): 259-272. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204593\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 21:44:38', created_at: '2013-05-24 21:12:19', )
