Comment.create(id: '1308', tool_id: '291', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information about Domeo is available via the following publications:</p> <p>Ciccarese P, Ocana M, Clark, T. \"Open semantic annotation of scientific publications using DOMEO.\" <em>Biomed Semantics</em> 2012 Apr 24;3 (Suppl 1):S1. <a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1186%2F2041-1480-3-S1-S1\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Ciccarese P, Ocana M, Castro LJG, Das S, Clark, T. \"An Open Annotation Ontology for Science on Web 3.0\". J <em>Biomed Semantics</em> 2011, 2 (Suppl 2):S4 (17 May 2011). <a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1186%2F2041-1480-2-S2-S4\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Ciccarese P, Ocana M, Clark, T. \"DOMEO: a web-based tool for semantic annotation of online documents.\"&nbsp; <em>Bio-Ontologies</em> 2011, Vienna, Austria. <a href=\"http://bio-ontologies.knowledgeblog.org/297\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Clark T, Ciccarese P, Attwood T, de Waard A and Pettifer S. \"A Round-Trip to the Annotation Store: Open, Transferable Semantic Annotation of Biomedical Publications.\" <em>Beyond the PDF</em> (workshop, January 19-21, 2011 University of California San Diego. <a href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/beyondthepdf/workshop-papers/clarkciccaresedewaardpettifer\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Ciccarese P, Ocana M, Das S, Clark T. \"AO: An Open Annotation Ontology for Science on the Web.\" <em>Bio-ontologies</em> 2010, Boston, USA. <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/wiki/images/c/c4/AO_paper_Bio-Ontologies_2010_preprint.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 22:29:08', created_at: '2013-06-04 17:50:47', )
