Comment.create(id: '1322', tool_id: '317', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>The developers on the PRORA series of programs:</p> <p>Glickman, Robert Jay. \"An Integrated Series of Computer Programs for Literary Research.<em>\" MLA, Conference 16</em>, 27 Dec. 1965.</p> <p>Glickman, Robert Jay and Gerrit Joseph Staalman. <em>Manual for the Printing of Literary Texts and Concordances by Computer: Preliminary Edition</em>. Toronto: University of Toronto Press, 1966.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Additional perspectives on PRORA and its applications:</p> <p>Lieberman, David. \"Reviews.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 1.1 (1966): 12. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00188014\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Burton, Dolores M. \"Automated Concordances and Word Indexes: The Process, The Programs, and the Products.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 15.3 (1981): 139-154. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007%2FBF02404180.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-12-19 23:58:40', created_at: '2013-06-14 17:22:03', )
Comment.create(id: '1323', tool_id: '318', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on SCAN and its use within the humanities can be found in the following:</p> <p>Brown, P.J. \"SCAN: A Simple Conversational Programming Language for Text Analysis.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 6.4 (1972): 223-227. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30204035\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Brown, P.J. <em>SCAN - A Sub-System for Document Searching</em>. Computing Laboratory, University of Kent at Canterbury, 1971. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2FBF02404273\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 22:35:21', created_at: '2013-06-14 19:43:40', )
Comment.create(id: '1324', tool_id: '319', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information on CLAS, its development and its application is available in the following articles:</p> <p>Borden, George A. and James J. Watts. \"A Computerized Language Analysis System.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.3 (1971): 129-141. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/30199396\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Waltman, Franklin M. \"C.L.A.S. and the Cantar de Mio Cid.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 10.3 (1976): 145-152. <a href=\"http://www.jstor.org/stable/i30204250\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2013-06-18 22:37:35', created_at: '2013-06-14 20:00:21', )
