Comment.create(id: '1526', tool_id: '483', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>More information about SNOBOL and its applications within the humanities is available in the following articles:</p> <p>Hsu, Robert W. \"A New String-Manipulating Lanuguage.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 2.5 (1968): 256-262. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402499\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Forte, Allen. \"The Programming Language SNOBOL3: An Introduction.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 1.5 (1967): 157-163. <a href=\"link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00055401\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Raskin, Jeffrey S. \"Programming Languages for the Humanities.\" Computers and the Humanities 5.3 (1971): 155-158. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402180\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Turner, Ronald C. \"Letter to the Editor.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 4.1 (1969): 74. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02393453\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Wachal, Robert S. \"The Machine in the Garden: Computers and literary scholarship, 1970.\" Computers and the Humanities 5.1 (1970): 23-28. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404254\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-17 18:28:00', created_at: '2014-07-10 20:53:20', )
Comment.create(id: '1527', tool_id: '484', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>Please see the following papers for more information on FORTRAN in relation to Humanities scholarship:</p> <p><span>Allwright, Christine. \"Software Review: FISHER: A String-Handling Package.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 10.5 (1976): 297-298. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007%2FBF02420064.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</span></p> <p>Dilligan, Robert J. \"Introductory FORTRAN textbooks: An Overview for Humanists.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 7.6 (1973): 399-406. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02395115\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Kline, Edward A. \"A Computer-Assisted Graphemic Analysis of <em>Beowulf</em>: Purpose and Procedure.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 2.5 (1968): 211-213. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402493\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Koster, Patricia. \"Words and Numbers: A Quantitative Approach to Swift and Some Understrappers.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 4.5 (1970): 289-304. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02400251\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Silva, Georgette. \"Phontrns: An Automatic Orthographic-to-Phonetic Conversion System for French.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 3.5 (1969) 257-265. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404166\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p><span>Sowa, Cora Angier and John F. Sowa. \"Thought Clusters in Early Greek Oral Poetry.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 8.3 (1974): 131-146. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402131\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</span></p> <p>Turner, Ronald C. \"Letter to the Editor.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 4.1 (1969): 74. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02393453\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-17 20:02:46', created_at: '2014-07-11 19:23:05', )
Comment.create(id: '1528', tool_id: '485', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>For an overview of programming languages used in the humanities in the late 1960s, including COMIT, pelase see the following article:</p> <p>Oakman, Robert L. \"New Course Established.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 3.4 (1969): 242. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02401459\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p>Wachal, Robert S. \"The Machine in the Garden: Computers and literary scholarship, 1970.\"<em> Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.1 (1970): 23-28. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404254\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-21 16:23:01', created_at: '2014-07-11 20:07:02', )
Comment.create(id: '1529', tool_id: '486', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>COBOL was often discussed in comparison to other programming languages by scholars interested in applying computer methods to research. For more information, please see the following papers:</p> <p>Raskin, Jeffrey F. \"Programming Languages for the Humanities.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.3 (1971): 155-158. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402180\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p><span>Wachal, Robert S. \"The Machine in the Garden: Computers and literary scholarship, 1970.\"<em> Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.1 (1970): 23-28. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404254\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>. </span></p>', updated_at: '2014-07-11 20:28:55', created_at: '2014-07-11 20:24:29', )
Comment.create(id: '1530', tool_id: '487', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>For more information about ALGOL in relation to humanities research, please see the following articles:</p> <p>\"New Courses Established.\" <span><em>Computers and the Humanities</em> </span>3.5 (1969): 270-271. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404169\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p><span><span>Burnard, L.D. \"Software Review: CLOC.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 14.4 (1980): 259-260. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404435\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</span></span></p> <p><span>Hanon, Suzanne. \"The Study of English Loan-Words in Modern French.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 7.6 (1973): 389-398. <a href=\"er.com/article/10.1007/BF02395114\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</span></p> <p>Raskin, Jeffrey F. \"Programming Languages for the Humanities.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.3 (1971): 155-158. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402180\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p> <p><span>Raskin, Jeffrey F. \"Request for Algorithms.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 4.3 (1970): 219. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402242\">Web</a>.</span></p> <p><span>Wachal, Robert S. \"The Machine in the Garden: Computers and literary scholarship, 1970.\"<em> Computers and the Humanities</em> 5.1 (1970): 23-28. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02404254\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>. </span></p> <p><span>Wachal, Robert S. \"Uphill Introduction.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 4.3 (1970) 205-207. <span><a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02402242\">Web</a>.</span><br /></span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-21 16:29:07', created_at: '2014-07-11 20:49:35', )
Comment.create(id: '1531', tool_id: '489', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>For an example of how EULER was used in Humanities research, please see the following paper:</p> <p>Parsons, I. T. \"String Manipulation with Extended Euler.\" <em>Computers and the Humanities</em> 10.3 (1976): 173-179. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF02426303\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>.</p>', updated_at: '2014-07-14 18:39:09', created_at: '2014-07-14 18:36:50', )
Comment.create(id: '1532', tool_id: '490', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>For more information about PL/C in relation to humanistic research applications, please see the following article:</p> <p>&nbsp;Hockey, Susan. \"Review: <em>Programming for the Liberal Arts: An Introduction to PL/C.</em>\" Computers and the Humanities 21.4 (1987): 264-265. <a href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00517815\" target=\"_blank\">Web</a>. </p>', updated_at: '2014-07-14 19:10:50', created_at: '2014-07-14 19:08:17', )
