Comment.create(id: '1541', tool_id: '507', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>The Discursis development team also maintains a page listing their published articles on the development and applications of the Discursis software. Please see their <a href=\"http://www.discursis.com/index.php/news-and-research/\" target=\"_blank\">Research page</a> for the full listing.</p>', updated_at: '2014-09-29 18:24:00', created_at: '2014-09-29 18:23:14', )
Comment.create(id: '1542', tool_id: '439', user_id: '569', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>I recently used RQDA for a small project where I read through around 600 news media articles. In the past I had used costly programs like Nvivo, so getting used to RQDA\'s interface was a bit of a change. However, the program is quite straightforward to use and you can watch some useful tutorials on youtube, or by following this link: <strong>http://tinyurl.com/nxa5c8x</strong></p> <p>While RQDA is not as feature rich as paid programs like Nvivo it will do the trick for organizing textual extracts by themes and subthemes. You may want to try a number of different approaches to importing your text as well. I started with a large pdf and tried to import the text, but there were erroneous sybols, tabs, and other formatting issues. Rather than work to fix these I just analyzed my texts with the mess that I imported. In all, RQDA is a useful tool and I will likely use it again in the future. I also expect that with repeated exposure to the program I will find it more useful and easier to work with.</p>', updated_at: '2014-10-02 16:08:00', created_at: '2014-10-02 16:08:00', )
Comment.create(id: '1543', tool_id: '9', user_id: '15', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>This tool is really neat, but it isn\'t as reliable as others. You need to fiddle with it and double click things.</p>', updated_at: '2014-10-03 18:39:19', created_at: '2014-10-03 18:39:19', )
