Comment.create(id: '1554', tool_id: '368', user_id: '9', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>Google Charts can also be used to handle RDF data. The Data-gov Wiki from the Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute has provided a tutorial for converting CSV data to RDF and then use Google Charts to visualize it at <a href=\"http://data-gov.tw.rpi.edu/wiki/How_to_use_Google_Visualization_API\" target=\"_blank\">http://data-gov.tw.rpi.edu/wiki/How_to_use_Google_Visualization_API</a></p> <p>Data-gov has also made nearly 300 RDF datasets available for wide use, which may be found at <a href=\"http://data-gov.tw.rpi.edu/wiki/Data.gov_Catalog\" target=\"_blank\">http://data-gov.tw.rpi.edu/wiki/Data.gov_Catalog</a></p>', updated_at: '2015-02-09 19:20:25', created_at: '2015-02-09 19:15:45', )
Comment.create(id: '1555', tool_id: '201', user_id: '764', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>Further more information can be found at:</p> <p><a href=\"http://tustep.wikispaces.com/\">http://tustep.wikispaces.com</a> (a wiki with practical examples and solutions for beginners and advanced users)</p> <p>as well as at</p> <p><a href=\"http://itug.de/\">http://itug.de/</a> (International TUSTEP User Group).</p>', updated_at: '2015-03-17 22:28:44', created_at: '2015-03-17 22:28:44', )
Comment.create(id: '1556', tool_id: '201', user_id: '768', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>The classical TUSTEP is a line based, parameter-driven programming language.</p> <p>But there is also TUSCRIPT, the highly developed, extremely flexible and efficient scripting language of TUSTEP, in particular suitable for processing text data, especially in SGML/XML. Examples for programming with TUSCRIPT can also be found in the Rosetta Code Wiki (<a href=\"http://rosettacode.org/wiki/Category:TUSCRIPT\">http://rosettacode.org/wiki/Category:TUSCRIPT</a>).</p> <p>In addition, there is TXSTEP, the XML-based interface for TUSTEP.</p> <p>For further information see http://tustep.wikispaces.com</p> <p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', updated_at: '2015-03-18 14:15:53', created_at: '2015-03-18 14:13:10', )
Comment.create(id: '1557', tool_id: '437', user_id: '866', is_pinned: '1', is_hidden: '0', index: '0', content: '<p>Hello,&nbsp;</p> <p>I am a developper of this tool. &nbsp;I would like to announce that we have the detailed manual in English language.&nbsp;</p> <p><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/p/khc/wiki/\">https://sourceforge.net/p/khc/wiki/</a></p> <p>Well, it may<span>&nbsp;need some refinements, but we have it now.</span></p>', updated_at: '2015-08-16 14:24:50', created_at: '2015-08-16 14:24:50', )
